tasks.details:
In `scripts/game_controller.gd`, add `_input(event)` or `_process(delta)` with Input polling:
- Map Input.is_action_pressed("ui_up") or KEY_W → Vector2i.UP
- Map Input.is_action_pressed("ui_down") or KEY_S → Vector2i.DOWN
- Map Input.is_action_pressed("ui_left") or KEY_A → Vector2i.LEFT
- Map Input.is_action_pressed("ui_right") or KEY_D → Vector2i.RIGHT
- Call `snake.set_direction(new_dir)` which already handles reversal rejection
- In GAME_OVER state, any key press calls `reset_game()`

Define input actions in project.godot if not using default ui_* actions:
```ini
[input]
move_up={"key": "W", "key": "Up"}
move_down={"key": "S", "key": "Down"}
move_left={"key": "A", "key": "Left"}
move_right={"key": "D", "key": "Right"}
```

Pseudo-code:
```gdscript
func _process(_delta):
    if state == GameState.GAME_OVER:
        if Input.is_anything_pressed(): reset_game()
        return
    if Input.is_action_pressed("ui_up"): snake.set_direction(Vector2i.UP)
    elif Input.is_action_pressed("ui_down"): snake.set_direction(Vector2i.DOWN)
    elif Input.is_action_pressed("ui_left"): snake.set_direction(Vector2i.LEFT)
    elif Input.is_action_pressed("ui_right"): snake.set_direction(Vector2i.RIGHT)
```
